description:
TECHNICAL SKILLS
Overall 08– 10 years of professional experience;
Able to create / develop a compelling story to answer business questions using analytics outcomes;
Hands on programming experience in R (Mandatory); Python and PySpark (Desirable);
Should have worked on data heavy projects on Natural Language Processing(NLP), risk scoring, Propensity / Classification Modeling, Segmentation, Promotion Analytics, Campaign Optimization, recommender engines, fraud analytics, etc.
Great analytical skills, with expertise in Deep Learning, Machine Learning methods such as CNN, RNN, Autoencoder, SVM, Naïve Bayes Classifier, Decision Trees, Random Forest, PCA etc. is MUST;
Experience in Artificial Intelligence / Cognitive Computing / OpenCV highly desirable.CLIENT MANAGEMENT SKILLS
Must possess good client facing experience with the ability to facilitate requirements sessions and lead teams and present analysis in business terms;
Must have led / managed / executed Machine Learning driven project through the complete life-cycle of the project;
Any demonstrable experience in cross-selling / up-selling / farming existing clients will be a big plus;DESIRED EDUCATIONAL BACKGROUND
Masters or Ph.D. in Statistics / Econometrics / Operations Research / Artificial Intelligence;OTHER DESIRED ATTRIBUTES
Confident and self-starter;
Must possess a detail-oriented approach;
Ability to adapt and thrive in the fast-paced environment;
Good written and oral/ presentation skills;
Willing to travel and adapt to different client environment
